## 3. Core DAO Layer

**Package:** `com.passwordvault.core.dao`

I built the persistence layer for the two main domain objects — categories and password entries. Both extend `BaseDAO` from the infrastructure layer.

### `CategoryDAO` (`core/dao/`)
- `create(Category)` — inserts a new category row and writes the generated `id` back into the passed `Category` object using `RETURN_GENERATED_KEYS`
- `getByUserId(int userId)` — returns all categories belonging to the current user as a `List<Category>`
- Each category maps to the `Category` model: `id`, `userId`, `name`, `description`

### `PasswordEntryDAO` (`core/dao/`)
- Full **CRUD** implementation for password entries
- `create(PasswordEntry)` — inserts a new entry (website, username, encrypted password, categoryId, notes) and writes back the generated `id`
- `getAllByUserId(int userId)` — fetches all entries for the logged-in user, including `created_date` and `updated_date` timestamps
- `update(PasswordEntry)` — updates all mutable fields and sets `updated_date = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP` atomically in SQL
- `delete(int id)` — removes an entry by primary key
- Passwords are stored **already encrypted** — `PasswordEntryDAO` never sees plaintext; encryption/decryption happens in the service layer before reaching this DAO

